name: Slow Cooker Chicken Enchilada Soup
author: Sabbath Jackson
summary: Not quite a tortilla soup, not quite a taco soup, this comes together fast and gets better overnight. Stores like a dream and has fabulous flavor. Serve with sour cream and cheese on top, with either tortilla chips or cornbread on the side. Or if you're feeling fancy, you could make some paninis with pepper Jack cheese, roasted red peppers, avocados, tomatoes and mushrooms. Very tasty!
ingredients: 2 (10 ounce) cans diced tomatoes with green chile peppers
1 (8 ounce) package red enchilada sauce (such as Frontera®)
directions: Mix chicken broth, black beans, diced tomatoes, pale ale, corn, red enchilada sauce, onion,  , and jalapeno pepper together in a slow cooker
Cook on Low until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of the chicken reads at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C), 5 to 6 hours
Remove chicken and shred using 2 forks; stir back into the slow cooker
Stir cilantro into the slow cooker
Cook on Low until flavors combine, about 15 minutes
